BT 0.25 g /F4 11 Tf 72 658 Td (Michelle Obama grew up in a modest home where every dollar was carefully) Tj ET
BT 0.25 g /F4 11 Tf 72 643 Td (considered. Her parents taught her the difference between wanting something and) Tj ET
BT 0.25 g /F4 11 Tf 72 628 Td (needing it. This discipline helped her become debt-free and financially secure) Tj ET
BT 0.25 g /F4 11 Tf 72 613 Td (long before the White House.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F2 12 Tf 72 583 Td (THE LESSON) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 565 Td (Needs are things essential for survival and basic functioning: food, shelter,) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 551 Td (clothing, healthcare, transportation to school. Wants are everything else: the) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 537 Td (latest phone, brand-name clothes, entertainment.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 515 Td (The 24-hour rule: when you want to buy something non-essential, wait 24 hours.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 501 Td (If you still want it tomorrow, consider it. This simple rule prevents impulse) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 487 Td (purchases that you regret.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 465 Td (Marketing is designed to make wants FEEL like needs. Companies spend billions) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 451 Td (making you believe you cannot live without their product. Being media literate) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 437 Td (means recognizing manipulation.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 415 Td (Distinguishing wants from needs is not about never treating yourself. It is) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 401 Td (about making CONSCIOUS choices. Sometimes choosing the want is perfectly fine.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 72 387 Td (The key is that it is a choice, not an impulse.) Tj ET

